description: There is a Big 5 model in psychology and a questionnaire corresponding to that. The questionnaire consists of 44 questions and depending on the user's answers to those questions, the user's personality can be identified. title: machine learning
description:
A personality prediction website/app needs to be developed

There is a Big 5 model in psychology and a questionnaire corresponding to that. The questionnaire consists of 44 questions and depending on the users answers to those questions, the users personality can be identified. The answers for each question is numeric value from 1 to 5. After the person's personality is detected, we also have to recommend songs/music to improve personality of the person. 

https://arc.psych.wisc.edu/self-report/big-five-inventory-bfi/

This link consists of the questionnaire as well as the formula to calculate the scores on the basis of the answers to the questions

Then this data has to be passed to a Machine Learning model which will narrow down the person's personality from 5 factors to a single factor.
The github link consists of a dataset and a logistic regression model. We can implement a better model like SVM and then display it on the flask app.
https://github.com/vidushi4/Personality-prediction-system

This web interface of this system can be built on any tech stack
subject_tags: ["Machine Learning,Full Stack Web Development,Backend web development,Data science and machine learning"]
